mat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmericans%20produce%2040%20million%20tons%20of%20plastic%20waste%20each%20year.%20And%20it%20has%20to%20go%20somewhere.%20%3Cp%3ECarl%20Godfrey%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAmerica%20has%20long%20had%20a%20plastic%20problem.%20It's%20an%20urgent%20question%20%E2%80%94%20what%20do%20we%20do%20with%20the%2040%20million%20tons%20of%20plastic%20waste%20we%20produce%20annually%3F%20One%20year%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisposable-face-mask-waste-toxic-poison-water-nanoplastics-pollution-health-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplastic%20waste%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20roughly%20enough%20to%20smother%20the%20entirety%20of%20Manhattan%20a%20meter%20deep%2C%20and%20it%20has%20to%20go%20somewhere.%20For%20years%2C%20the%20answer%20was%20simple%3A%20Make%20a%20lot%20of%20it%2C%20dump%20most%20of%20it%20in%20the%20landfill%2C%20and%20make%20the%20rest%20of%20it%20someone%20else's%20problem%20%E2%80%94%20the%20US%20regularly%20exported%207%20million%20tons%20a%20year%20to%20China%20alone.%20Some%20of%20it%20was%20melted%20into%20lesser%20plastic%3B%20the%20rest%20was%20incinerated%20or%20buried.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20then%2C%20in%202018%2C%20China%20cut%20off%20plastic%20imports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20America%20is%20coming%20to%20terms%20with%20a%20hard%20truth%3A%20Plastic%20was%20never%20designed%20to%20be%20recycled%20and%20there's%20no%20profitable%20way%20to%20recycle%2091%25%20of%20it.%20The%20environmental%20impacts%20have%20been%20disastrous.%20About%20430%20million%20tons%20of%20plastic%20are%20produced%20globally%20every%20year%2C%20accounting%20for%2014%25%20of%20global%20oil%20demand.%20The%20refinement%20of%20plastic%20alone%20emits%20up%20to%20235%20million%20tons%20of%20greenhouse%20gases%20a%20year.%20Most%20of%20that%20plastic%20breaks%20down%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicroplastics-risks-heart-attack-stroke-study-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emicroplastics%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20make%20their%20way%20into%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexpert-how-i-keep-baby-family-safe-toxic-plastic-microplastics-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eair%2C%20rain%2C%20and%20our%20bodies%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Almost%2095%25%20of%20America's%20water%20supply%20contains%20plastic%20fibers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20US%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20and%20other%20European%20countries%20responded%20to%20China's%20ban%20by%20sending%20their%20waste%20to%20places%20like%20Thailand%20and%20Malaysia%2C%20those%20countries%20then%20followed%20China%20in%20cutting%20off%20waste%20imports.%20The%20message%20was%20clear%3A%20The%20Global%20South%20would%20no%20longer%20be%20a%20dumping%20ground%20for%20the%20West.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20scavenger%20drinks%20water%20while%20collecting%20plastic%20waste%20to%20sell%20to%20a%20recycling%20center%20at%20a%20landfill%20in%20Medan%2C%20North%20Sumatra%2C%20Indonesia%20in%20March%202024%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6621639320b15f0ff4294511%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFor%20decades%2C%20America%20sent%20its%20plastic%20waste%20to%20countries%20like%20China%20and%20Indonesia.%20%3Cp%3EKartik%20Byma%2FAFP%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAmerica%20is%20now%20scrambling%20to%20find%20alternatives.%20One%20approach%20peddled%20by%20oil%20corporations%20like%20Chevron%20and%20Exxon%20has%20been%20to%20turn%20plastic%20into%20crude%20oil%2C%20which%20they%20say%20extends%20the%20life%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnorth-americas-largest-waste-hauler-investing-in-a-plastic-recycler-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplastic%20that%20would've%20otherwise%20ended%20up%20in%20a%20landfill%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20these%20companies%20look%20to%20replace%20projected%20lost%20revenue%20from%20the%20phasing%20out%20of%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20they're%20lobbying%20to%20blanket%20the%20country%20with%20150%20plants%20that%20specialize%20in%20pyrolysis%2C%20a%20form%20of%20chemical%20recycling%20that%20melts%20plastic%20down%20into%20crude%20oil%20to%20be%20used%20for%20fuel%20and%20petrochemicals%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20make%20lesser-quality%20plastics.%20While%20advocates%20champion%20these%20facilities%20for%20breaking%20down%20hard-to-recycle%20plastics%20that%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-recycling-startups-aluminum-plastic-valuable-materials-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecyclers%20toss%20aside%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20critics%20condemn%20them%20for%20emitting%20toxic%20particles%2C%20relying%20heavily%20on%20government%20subsidies%2C%20and%20acting%20as%20a%20greenwashed%20alternative%20to%20addressing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplastic-recycled-into-bricks-ivory-coast-conceptos-plasticos-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20plastic%20problem%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20they're%20pitched%20as%20an%20innovation%20set%20to%20bring%20us%20a%20%26quot%3Bcircular%20economy%26quot%3B%20of%20plastic%20that%20allows%20us%20to%20stop%20making%20new%20plastic%20and%20just%20reuse%20what%20we%20have%2C%20marketing%20for%20pyrolysis%20and%20recycling%20overlooks%20a%20glaring%20fact%3A%20Plastic%20%3Cem%3Eproduction%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgrist.org%2Fclimate%2Ffossil-fuel-companies-are-counting-on-plastics-to-save-them%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoubles%20every%2015%20to%2020%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20sustainable%2C%20Tim%20Miller%2C%20a%20vice%20president%20at%20the%20Ohio%20plastic-recycling%20center%20Royal%20Paper%20Stock%2C%20told%20me%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20stop%20it.%26quot%3B%20Pyrolysis%20is%20another%20sign%20of%20America's%20plastic%20paralysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20years%20after%20World%20War%20II%2C%20plastic%20flooded%20the%20marketplace%20as%20a%20cheap%20alternative%20to%20otherwise%20scarce%20and%20finite%20materials.%20It%20was%20hailed%20as%20a%20democratic%20harbinger%20of%20a%20new%2C%20utopian%20age%20of%20capitalism%2C%20fueling%20the%20subsequent%20decades%20of%20cheap%20consumerism%20that%20became%20synonymous%20with%20the%20American%20dream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20continuous%20flow%20of%20oil%20fueled%20not%20just%20cars%20but%20an%20entire%20culture%20based%20on%20the%20consumption%20of%20new%20products%20made%20of%20plastics%2C%26quot%3B%20Susan%20Freinkel%20wrote%20in%20her%20book%20%26quot%3BPlastic%3A%20A%20Toxic%20Love%20Story.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlastic%20went%20from%20being%20practically%20nonexistent%20in%201940%20to%20being%20consumed%20at%20a%20rate%20of%2030%20pounds%20a%20person%20each%20year%20by%201960.%20Just%20as%20quickly%2C%20it%20became%20a%20target%20of%20environmental%20movements%20protesting%20litter%2C%20garbage-filled%20oceans%2C%20and%20landfills%20brimming%20with%20plastic.%20Oil%20and%20chemical%20companies%20responded%20by%20looking%20into%20whether%20recycling%20was%20realistic%20or%2C%20more%20importantly%2C%20profitable.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2020%2F09%2F11%2F897692090%2Fhow-big-oil-misled-the-public-into-believing-plastic-would-be-recycled%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIt%20wasn't%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%20companies%20shifted%20the%20blame%20for%20the%20pollution%20onto%20consumers.%20The%20%26quot%3BCrying%20Indian%26quot%3B%20commercial%2C%20funded%20by%20beverage%20and%20packaging%20corporations%2C%20aired%20in%201971%2C%20showing%20a%20Native%20American%20character%20crying%20at%20the%20sight%20of%20litter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20messaging%20worked.%20As%20companies%20expanded%20plastic%20into%20every%20facet%20of%20life%2C%20recycling%20became%20the%20due%20diligence%20needed%20to%20sustain%20our%20hyperconsumption.%20We%20didn't%20worry%20about%20plastic%20bottles%20because%20the%20recycling%20truck%20carried%20them%20off%20to%20a%20new%20life.%20Companies%20like%20Coca-Cola%20and%20Nestl%C3%A9%20slapped%20%26quot%3B100%25%20recycled%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3B100%25%20recyclable%26quot%3B%20labels%20on%20their%20packaging%20to%20appear%20sustainable.%20Just%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Plastics%20Industry%20Association%20launched%20a%20million-dollar%20ad%20campaign%2C%20%26quot%3BRecycling%20Is%20Real%2C%26quot%3B%20claiming%20that%20it's%20%26quot%3Bnot%20only%20real%2C%20but%20feasible%20and%20economical.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20recycling%20%3Cem%3Eis%3C%2Fem%3E%20real%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20plastic%20isn't%20recycled%2C%20mostly%20due%20to%20how%20expensive%20it%20is%20to%20clean%20and%20sort%20it%20effectively.%20A%202022%20report%20by%20the%20Organization%20for%20Economic%20Co-operation%20and%20Development%20found%20only%209%25%20of%20all%20plastic%20ever%20produced%20had%20been%20recycled%3B%2072%25%20ended%20up%20in%20landfills%20or%20the%20environment.%20Unlike%20aluminum%20or%20glass%2C%20the%20plastic%20that%20%3Cem%3Ecan%3C%2Fem%3E%20be%20recycled%20rarely%20results%20in%20replacing%20one%20recycled%20water%20bottle%20with%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Recycling%20sorters%20at%20Recologys%20Recycle%20Central%20sort%20out%20pieces%20of%20flimsy%20and%20film%20plastic%20destined%20for%20landfill%20in%202019%20in%20San%20Francisco%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6621626110c6b0cde5f0d63a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERecycling%20workers%20in%20San%20Francisco%20sort%20out%20flimsy%20plastic%20that%20cannot%20be%20recycled.%3Cp%3ELea%20Suzuki%2FSan%20Francisco%20Chronicle%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20it's%20a%20process%20of%20downcycling%20%E2%80%94%20turning%20plastic%20into%20lesser%20plastics%20like%20plant%20containers%20or%20bins%20before%20they%20are%20relegated%20to%20a%20landfill.%20By%20downcycling%20a%20tiny%20portion%20of%20plastic%20waste%2C%20companies%20can%20genuinely%20reuse%20a%20relatively%20small%20share%20of%20plastic%2C%20while%20convincing%20consumers%20that%20the%20industry%20has%20created%20a%20circular%20economy%20of%20infinitely%20recycled%20plastic.%20Never%20mind%20that%20products%20advertised%20as%20being%20made%20from%20recycled%20plastic%20are%20made%20almost%20entirely%20out%20of%20new%20plastic%20or%20that%20almost%20all%20the%20300%20pounds%20of%20plastic%20every%20American%20consumes%20each%20year%20(10%20times%20as%20much%20as%20in%201960)%20ends%20up%20in%20a%20landfill%2C%20in%20the%20ocean%2C%20or%20incinerated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELarry%20Thomas%2C%20a%20former%20president%20of%20what's%20now%20called%20the%20Plastics%20Industry%20Association%2C%20told%20NPR%20in%202020%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20public%20thinks%20that%20recycling%20is%20working%2C%20then%20they%20are%20not%20going%20to%20be%20as%20concerned%20about%20the%20environment.%26quot%3B%20And%20if%20they%20aren't%20worried%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20plastic%20on%20the%20environment%2C%20they%20won't%20threaten%20the%20plastics%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESince%202018%2C%20the%20fossil-fuel%20and%20plastics%20industries%20have%20faced%20two%20harsh%20realities%3A%20Oil%20is%20being%20phased%20out%20in%20favor%20of%20clean%2C%20renewable%20energy%2C%20and%20plastic%20waste%20can%20no%20longer%20be%20exported%20to%20developing%20nations%20in%20the%20South.%20To%20replace%20their%20fuel%20losses%2C%20oil%20companies%20are%20going%20all%20in%20on%20plastic.%20The%20International%20Energy%20Agency%20predicted%20in%202018%20that%20petrochemical%20products%20like%20plastic%20would%20outpace%20trucks%2C%20aviation%2C%20and%20shipping%20in%20oil%20demand%20by%202050.%20In%20a%20recent%20report%2C%20ExxonMobil%20predicted%20that%20petrochemicals%20used%20largely%20for%20plastics%20and%20fertilizer%20would%20account%20for%20nearly%20all%20of%20the%20oil%20industry's%20growth%20by%202050%2C%20replacing%20industrial%20fuel%20demand%2C%20which%20is%20projected%20to%20decrease.%20To%20keep%20expanding%20plastic%20production%2C%20however%2C%20it%20needs%20to%20look%20sustainable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Good%20Year%20sign%20in%20Akron%2C%20Ohio%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662160d010c6b0cde5f0d535%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAkron%20built%20its%20economy%20on%20polymers%20like%20rubber%20and%20plastic.%3Cp%3ETaylor%20Dorrell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAkron%2C%20Ohio%2C%20which%20hosts%20about%20one-quarter%20of%20the%20country's%20polymer%20companies%2C%20is%20ground%20zero%20for%20this%20push.%20Designated%20by%20the%20Biden%20administration%20as%20the%20only%20%26quot%3Btech%20hub%26quot%3B%20in%20Ohio%2C%20the%20city%20has%20received%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20from%20the%20CHIPS%20Act%2C%20which%20it%20hopes%20to%20use%20to%20create%20a%20circular%20economy%20around%20plastic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202012%2C%20Alterra%20Energy%20opened%20America's%20first%20large-scale%20plastic-pyrolysis%20facility.%20According%20to%20its%20website%2C%20Alterra%20converts%20%26quot%3Bplastics%20back%20into%20their%20original%20building%20blocks%20to%20produce%20new%20plastics%20and%20other%20valuable%20products.%26quot%3B%20The%20crude%20oil%20produced%20by%20the%20Akron%20facility%20is%20shipped%20to%20petrochemical%20companies%20around%20the%20globe%20to%20be%20purified%20and%20made%20into%20new%20plastics.%20But%20it's%20unclear%20how%20effective%20this%20process%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20study%20published%20in%202023%20by%20researchers%20at%20the%20National%20Renewable%20Energy%20Laboratory%20found%20that%20the%20economic%20and%20environmental%20impact%20of%20turning%20pyrolysis%20oil%20back%20into%20plastic%20was%20actually%20far%20worse%20than%20it%20was%20to%20make%20brand-new%20plastic.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20they%20said%2C%20pyrolysis%20oil%20is%20%26quot%3Btypically%20reintegrated%20into%20the%20petrochemical%20industry%20where%20only%20a%20small%20fraction%20is%20used%20for%20closed-loop%20recycling.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Alterra%20Energy%20facility%20in%20Akron%2C%20Ohio%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6621607a10c6b0cde5f0d511%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Alterra%20facility%20in%20Akron%20promises%20to%20recycle%20plastic%20infinitely.%20But%20that's%20not%20actually%20happening.%20%3Cp%3ETaylor%20Dorrell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20has%20had%2C%20let's%20say%2C%20limited%20success%2C%26quot%3B%20Miller%2C%20the%20Royal%20Paper%20Stock%20vice%20president%2C%20said%20about%20pyrolysis.%20%26quot%3BNo%20one%20yet%20in%20the%20United%20States%20that%20I%20know%20of%20is%20just%20cranking%20in%20plastic%20and%20pumping%20out%20oil.%26quot%3B%20He%20pointed%20to%20a%20pyrolysis%20facility%20in%20Oregon%20that%20just%20announced%20it%20would%20shut%20down%20after%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResidents%20in%20Akron%20are%20split%20on%20the%20impacts%20of%20the%20Alterra%20facility.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20pyrolysis%20melts%20plastic%20to%20be%20reused%20instead%20of%20sending%20it%20to%20the%20landfill%20or%20incinerator.%20On%20the%20other%2C%20it%20emits%20cancerous%20pollutants%20such%20as%20mercury%2C%20benzene%2C%20and%20arsenic%2C%20and%20props%20up%20the%20very%20fossil-fuel%20companies%20that%20are%20driving%20the%20climate%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kelley%20Sayre%20in%20front%20of%20her%20garage%20in%20Akron%2C%20Ohio%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6621604320b15f0ff429439e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20Akron%20residents%2C%20like%20Kelley%20Sayre%2C%20are%20not%20happy%20about%20the%20pyrolysis%20facility.%3Cp%3ETaylor%20Dorrell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAkron's%20going%20for%20'the%20green%20city%20on%20the%20hill%2C'%26quot%3B%20Kelley%20Sayre%2C%20a%20fourth-generation%20Akron%20resident%2C%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20it's%20really%20'the%20greenwashing%20city.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVicky%20Abou-Ghalioum%2C%20the%20lead%20petrochemicals%20organizer%20of%20Buckeye%20Environmental%20Network%2C%20has%20been%20working%20with%20Akron%20residents%20concerned%20about%20the%20environmental%20and%20health%20impacts%20of%20chemical%20recycling%2C%20but%20it's%20proved%20challenging%20in%20a%20city%20ruled%20by%20polymers.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20afraid%20to%20talk%20about%20plastic%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%20Her%20organization%20has%20been%20pushing%20the%20EPA%20to%20address%20the%20influx%20of%20planned%20pyrolysis%20facilities%20in%20Ohio%2C%20arguing%20that%20they're%20bad%20for%20the%20environment%20and%20people%2C%20and%20aren't%20even%20profitable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Alterra%20Energy%20said%20its%20Akron%20facility%20is%20profitable%20and%20diverts%20over%20100%2C000%20pounds%20of%20plastic%20each%20day%20from%20landfills.%20%26quot%3BWe%20operate%20in%20a%20heavily%20regulated%20industry%20and%20are%20in%20compliance%20with%20those%20requirements%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said%20in%20response%20to%20concerns%20about%20toxic%20emissions.%20It%20also%20said%20one%20of%20its%20customers%20uses%20Alterra's%20oil%20product%20exclusively%20for%20making%20new%20plastic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20problems%20of%20pyrolysis%2C%20many%20manufacturers%20hail%20it%20as%20a%20sustainable%20miracle.%20Companies%20such%20as%20Eastman%20Chemical%20Co.%20see%20chemical%20recycling%20as%20the%20solution%20to%20recycling%20or%20composting%2050%25%20of%20their%20plastic%20packaging%20by%202025%2C%20and%20the%20American%20Chemistry%20Council%20claims%20the%20growing%20industry%20is%20necessary%20for%20fostering%20what%20it%20calls%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanchemistry.com%2Fchemistry-in-america%2Fnews-trends%2Fpress-release%2F2022%2Famerica-s-plastic-makers-encourage-congressional-focus-on-advanced-recycling-to-achieve-circularity%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplastics%20circularity%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20But%20these%20companies%20face%20an%20uphill%20battle.%20Former%20Mayor%20Mike%20Bloomberg%20of%20New%20York%20City%20launched%20an%20%2485%20million%20campaign%20in%202022%20to%20stop%20over%20120%20proposed%20petrochemical%20facilities.%20%26quot%3BPetrochemical%20plants%20poison%20our%20air%20and%20water%20%E2%80%94%20killing%20Americans%20and%20harming%20the%20health%20of%20entire%20communities%2C%26quot%3B%20Bloomberg%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20plastic-recycling%20industry%2C%20pyrolysis%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20well%20funded%20but%20failing%20experiment.%20A%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.beyondplastics.org%2Fpublications%2Fchemical-recycling%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Beyond%20Plastics%20and%20the%20International%20Pollutants%20Elimination%20Network%20found%20that%20the%2011%20pyrolysis%20facilities%20in%20operation%20in%20the%20US%20required%20massive%20public%20subsidies%2C%20most%20couldn't%20operate%20at%20full%20capacity%2C%20and%20only%20two%20of%20the%20plants%20sold%20the%20crude%20oil%20to%20be%20used%20exclusively%20for%20plastic%20production.%20Most%20of%20it%20was%20sold%20to%20make%20fuels%20and%20chemicals.%20Based%20on%20their%20findings%2C%20they%20argued%20that%20pyrolysis%20was%20ultimately%20%26quot%3Ba%20public%20relations%20distraction%20to%20prevent%20plastic%20regulation%20and%20prop%20up%20the%20profits%20of%20the%20petrochemical%2Fplastics%20industry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20conundrum%20of%20plastic%20grows%20more%20dire%20by%20the%20day%2C%20there%20are%20signs%20of%20hope.%20In%20early%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unep.org%2Fnews-and-stories%2Fpress-release%2Fhistoric-day-campaign-beat-plastic-pollution-nations-commit-develop%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20UN%20adopted%20a%20resolution%20that%20could%20send%20shock%20waves%20throughout%20the%20entire%20plastic-disposing%20world.%20Heads%20of%20state%2C%20environment%20ministers%2C%20and%20UN%20representatives%20agreed%20to%20end%20all%20plastic%20pollution%20with%20a%20legally%20binding%20international%20plastic%20treaty%20to%20be%20officially%20adopted%20later%20this%20year.%20%26quot%3BPlastic%20pollution%20has%20grown%20into%20an%20epidemic%2C%26quot%3B%20Espen%20Barth%20Eide%2C%20Norway's%20then-minister%20for%20climate%20and%20the%20environment%2C%20said%20in%20the%20announcement.%20%26quot%3BWith%20today's%20resolution%20we%20are%20officially%20on%20track%20for%20a%20cure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20resolution%20would%20establish%20an%20agreement%20addressing%20plastic%20at%20every%20level%2C%20from%20production%20to%20recycling%2C%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20reduce%20plastic%20pollution%20worldwide.%20Organizations%20such%20as%20the%20international%20coalition%20Break%20Free%20From%20Plastic%20have%20said%20that%20cutting%20the%20production%20of%20plastic%20has%20to%20be%20on%20the%20table.%20%26quot%3BThe%20oil%20and%20gas%20industry%20sees%20plastic%20as%20its%20primary%20growth%20market%20and%20is%20investing%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20new%20and%20expanded%20facilities%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20organization%20wrote%20in%20a%202022%20statement.%20The%20group%20recommended%20bans%20on%20single-use%20plastics%2C%20a%20plastic%20tax%2C%20and%20regulations%20that%20prioritize%20plastics%20that%20can%20be%20recycled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BReduction%20in%20the%20production%20of%20plastic%20is%20entirely%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20Abou-Ghalioum%20of%20Buckeye%20Environmental%20Network%20told%20me.%20She%20pointed%20to%20the%20more%20than%20500%20cities%20and%2012%20states%20that%20have%20banned%20plastic%20bags%2C%20reducing%20the%20number%20of%20bags%20used%20by%20the%20billions.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20talked%20about%20how%20we%20rely%20on%20plastic%20for%20so%20many%20things%2C%20and%20it%20just%20feels%20like%20a%20marketing%20ploy%20to%20make%20us%20reluctant%20to%20shift%20away%20from%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20had%20everything%20we%20ever%20needed%20before%20plastic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tough%20reality%20is%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sustainabilitybynumbers.com%2Fp%2Flandfill-plastic-area%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E9.5%20billion%20tons%20of%20plastic%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20us%20will%20be%20here%20for%20hundreds%20of%20years.%20But%20how%20many%20millions%20of%20more%20tons%20are%20added%20will%20be%20determined%20by%20the%20types%20of%20solutions%20we%20arrive%20at%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Ftaylor-dorrell%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ETaylor%20Dorrell%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20writer%20and%20photographer%20based%20in%20Columbus%2C%20Ohio.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplastic-recycling-problem-america-waste-pyrolysis-big-oil-china-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713951301000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66184bb13f923f7dab0718