his%20year%20has%20been%20more%20engagement%2C%20more%20communications%2C%20but%20not%20more%20trust%2C%26quot%3B%20Ian%20Bremmer%2C%20the%20president%20and%20founder%20of%20the%20political-risk%20consultancy%20Eurasia%20Group%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Fvideos%2F2024-04-24%2Fbremmer-us-china-relations-getting-worse-quite-slowly-video%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%20TV%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20November%2C%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20China's%20leader%2C%20Xi%20Jinping%2C%20met%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-xi-pull-away-from-brink-conflict-apec-meeting-china-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAPEC%20summit%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20appearing%20keen%20to%20smooth%20over%20tensions.%20Bremmer%20said%20that%20since%20then%2C%20there'd%20been%20more%20stability%20in%20the%20US-China%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fmarkets%2Fus-treasurys-yellen-return-china-emphasize-excess-capacity-threat-2024-04-02%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJanet%20Yellen%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20US%20treasury%20secretary%2C%20visited%20China%20seeking%20cooperation%20in%20areas%20beneficial%20to%20both%20countries.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fchina-austin-military-pentagon-blinken-1f3923ce6284314ba38c101b6fee8b80%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELloyd%20Austin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20defense%20secretary%2C%20also%20spoke%20with%20China's%20defense%20minister%20last%20week.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fus-china-blinken-xi-middle-east-russia-210b07bcc585b9f2de14ff71951d8743%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAntony%20Blinken%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20secretary%20of%20state%2C%20is%20due%20in%20China%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rash%20of%20high-level%20meetings%20signals%20a%20thaw%20in%20US-China%20relations%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20the%20two%20don't%20agree%20with%20each%20other%20over%20many%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20means%20you%20still%20have%20plenty%20of%20areas%20that%20the%20countries%20are%20unhappy%20with%20each%20other%2C%20but%20when%20there%20is%20conflict%2C%20the%20conflict%20does%20not%20escalate%20out%20of%20control%20%E2%80%94%20rather%2C%20the%20escalations%20are%20targeted%20and%20calibrated%2C%26quot%3B%20Bremmer%20told%20Bloomberg%20TV.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20matter%20of%20seeing%20the%20glass%20as%20being%20half%20full%20or%20half%20empty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20we%20can%20say%20that%20the%20relationship%20is%20getting%20worse%2C%20it's%20true%2C%20but%20it's%20getting%20worse%20quite%20slowly%2C%20and%20there's%20more%20stability%20to%20the%20relationship%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bremmer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EUS-China%20communication%20has%20stabilized%20tensions%20over%20Taiwan%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20upside%20to%20increased%20communications%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%20is%20that%20the%20world's%20top%20two%20global%20powers%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20have%20a%20direct%20clash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20reason%20Washington%20and%20Beijing's%20tensions%20over%20Taiwan%20%E2%80%94%20which%20Beijing%20claims%20as%20its%20own%20territory%20%E2%80%94%20have%20been%20relatively%20stable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBremmer%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20US%20and%20China%20know%20each%20other's%20red%20lines%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20challenges%20in%20their%20relationship%20after%20decades%20of%20communication%2C%20making%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20nuanced%20calibrations%26quot%3B%20an%20easier%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20this%20understanding%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%20was%20why%20there%20was%20no%20%26quot%3Bstrong%20and%20sudden%20escalation%20that%20brought%20the%20two%20sides%20to%20crisis%26quot%3B%20after%20Taiwanese%20Vice%20President%20William%20Lai%20%E2%80%94%2